==English==

===Etymology===
From a metathetic variation of {{term|gird||to strike, smite, upbraid, scold, jibe|lang=en}}, from {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|girden|lang=enm}}, {{term|gerden||to strike, thrust, smite|lit=smite with a rod|lang=enm}}, from {{term|gerd|lang=enm}}, {{term|yerd||a rod, yard|lang=enm}}. More at {{l|en|yard}}.

